The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Government Railway police (GRP) on Monday recovered the second mobile phone of Arindam Manna, the GRP sub-inspector whose decapitated body was found beside the railway track near Sheoraphuli railway station on January 11. The cellphone was found near Hind Motor railway station near Howrah and didnt have a SIM card inside, said a GRP officer. The CID had recovered one of Mannas cellphones near his body. Manna had briefly investigated the death of Rizwanur Rahman, whose body was found under similar circumstances in September 2007.     The parents of a 19-month-old boy alleged that he died in Ramakrishna Mission Seva Pratishthan because of the negligence of the doctor who was treating him and other hospital staff. Ankit Datta was was admitted to the hospital on February 19 with high fever. His father, Subhash Dutta, alleged that repeated blood tests were carried out but the doctor could not identify the disease. Ankits aunt accused the nurses of incompetence. The nurses at the hospital denied the allegations and said the baby was weak.     B.K. Gupta, an IRS officer of the 1973 batch, took over as the chief commissioner of income tax, West Bengal, on February 28. He took over from T.K. Chatterjee.    B.G. Roy, the director of the Indo-German Chamber of Commerce in Calcutta, has been awarded the Cross of the Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany. The civilian honour is the German equivalent of the Padma Shri. A medal and charter signed by the German president were presented to Roy by German consul-general Gnter Wehrmann last week.     Clashes broke out between two student groups at Heramba Chandra College (South City) over the admission of students on Monday. Police said two the students hurled bricks at one another on the campus for two hours.     The body of Marjina Begam, 55, of Shyampur village in Howah, who was allegedly killed by her foster son Sheikh Akbar Ali on Friday, was exhumed on Monday and sent for a post-mortem. Ali had claimed his mother died of illness but some women spotted injury marks on the body during the last rites.     The foundation stone laying ceremony of the proposed elevated walkway between BBD Bag and Sealdah was cancelled after the model code of conduct came into effect on Monday. The event was scheduled for Tuesday as the transport department bosses had thought poll dates would be announced two days later, said an official of the department.            
